<exercise checkit-seed="0043" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>Q= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 3 &amp; -2 &amp; -4 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 &amp; -6 \\
-2 &amp; 1 &amp; -4 &amp; -4 \\
0 &amp; 2 &amp; -3 &amp; -5
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>Q^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-13 &amp; -10 &amp; -7 &amp; 28 \\
6 &amp; 4 &amp; 3 &amp; -12 \\
14 &amp; 11 &amp; 7 &amp; -30 \\
-6 &amp; -5 &amp; -3 &amp; 13
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

